added.title: Pop a Wheelie
added.description: Thomas and Diesel take a friendly competition too far and put an important delivery rescue at risk as they race across Sodor.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Goodbye, Ghost-Scaring Machine
added.description: Percy announces he's giving up his Ghost Scaring Machine - he's too old for it now. It soon becomes clear that the machine is good for more than just "scaring ghosts."
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Bully for Bugs
added.description: With Floyd's adult assistance, Baby Bugs and the Baby Looney Tunes learn an effective way to deal with a bully.

added.title: Sneaky Shoes
added.description: Pato, Pocoyo and Elly are having fun doing running and jumping competitions: except Pato is taking it very seriously. So when he loses he's mighty miffed. He is a very bad loser. He goes off in a huff and finds some swanky sneakers. He tries them on and discovers that these are no ordinary sneakers: they have a life of their own, they have super powers. Once he's mastered them he challenges Pocoyo and Elly to a re-match. Of course now he wins the running and jumping contests hands down. But Elly feels that something's up and doesn't want to compete anymore. When Pato tries to take the shoes off he realizes they won't undo. He's stuck and the shoes are going crazy. Luckily Caterpillar and Baby Bird save the day by getting the shoes off. And Pato has learnt that cheating just isn't a good way to win.

added.title: Shutterbug
added.description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird are bored of Pato's countless flower photos so they encourage him to take pictures of them instead. But each time Pato takes a photo, someone moves. Pato is exasperated because he wants to take perfect portraits but there's always something not quite right. Pato gives up. His friends put on an exhibition of his photos to show him that his pictures may not be exactly what he had in mind, but they really are wonderful because they capture the fun the friends have together.

added.title: Angry Alien
added.description: An angry alien finds his way to Pocoyo's world and declares that he wants to be king. Pocoyo, Elly and Caterpillar are all friendly but the alien just bosses them around and tries to scare them. When the alien tells Pato what to do, Pato finds it rather helpful. This goes against what the alien was expecting. Finally the alien is upset because he's not getting the reaction he wanted. He sobs and sobs. Pocoyo et al are concerned and kind. The alien realizes that he is likable, and if he'd just stop being so angry, he could have fun.

added.title: Pato Underwater
added.description: Pato packs his bag of toys and heads off to play with Octopus and Whale underwater. Unfortunately none of his toys work in the sea, and he doesn't like the food so he's all set to head back home. But then Whale shows Pato how fun things can be underwater once you get used to it. Pato has a wonderful time riding on Whale's back, bouncing on sea sponges and playing in a bubble. Finally Pocoyo and Elly arrive too and everyone has a splashy underwater party together.

added.title: Pato's Paintings
added.description: Everyone's preparing for a painting exhibition. Everyone except Pato who says he's not bothered about painting. When the show opens, Pato unexpectedly exhibits his paintings: they are amazing masterpieces (Actually they are real masterpieces. He didn't paint them!). Everyone is very impressed and asks him to paint another. But he can't, because in fact he cheated: he didn't paint these pictures at all. Pocoyo and the audience encourage Pato to have a go at painting. He paints a beautiful flower and feels very pleased with himself. His painting takes its place in the exhibition.

added.title: These Little Piggies Went to Market
added.description: Their first trip to a big grocery store fascinates the Baby Looney Tunes. After warning the others to stick to Granny's shopping list, Baby Bugs succumbs to buying a favorite treat then feels guilty.

added.title: Take Us Out to the Ballgame
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes experience their very first big stadium baseball game. Lola's favorite team's star batter gets her undivided attention until Lola's coaching affects the very outcome of the contest.

added.title: Now Museum, Now You Don't
added.description: Their very first trip to an art museum unleashes creative energy, turning the Baby Looney Tunes into enthused culture connoisseurs and budding artists. Baby Bugs recreates the museum experience back at Granny's house, finding abundant art history in everyday objects to the others' sheer delight.

added.title: Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind
added.description: Tweety feels neglected when no one wants him on their museum scavenger hunt team. Using his innate sleuthing abilities and the help of a friendly museum guard, Tweety proves to be the best scavenger hunter of them all. Once Tweety wins the contest, everyone wants him on their team.

added.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
added.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

added.title: Swing
added.description: Bing and Pando are taking turns on the swing. Bing counts to ten, but will Pando do the same?

added.title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
added.description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

added.title: Blocks
added.description: Bing is building a tower with his blocks but what will happen when both he and Coco want the last red block?

added.title: Ducks
added.description: Bing and Sula are feeding the ducks in the park, but will Bing remember to stand statue still?

added.title: Smoothie
added.description: It's snack time, but what will Bing and Flop make with the mushy banana?

added.title: Frog
added.description: Bing and Sula find a frog in the garden, but will Froggy like her new bucket house?

added.title: O'Little Tree
added.description: Mei shows Ella and Rishi the magic of Christmas - by growing an adorable Christmas tree in the middle of the farm.

added.title: Mountain
added.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

added.title: Chocolate Factory
added.description: Blippi's love for chocolate makes him wonder "How are chocolate bars made?" They head into a chocolate factory to find out, get a tour from Bard the Chocolate Bar, and FETCH gets a close-up look at the chocolate-making process!

added.title: Happy Place
added.description: Time to share some of the honey made at Lellobee City Farm with everyone that visits the farm

added.title: House Flies Don't Dance/Flying the Nest/The Insult
added.description: Lucas and Maizie help Findley learn to dance./ Arlo believes he's a big owl now, so it's time to fly his nest. But is Arlo ready to leave his friends behind?/ When Lucas calls Findley a mean name, he tries to make things right again.

added.title: I'll Do it in a Minute/Cloud Gazing/Don't Do That Arlo
added.description: Arlo has fun playing, but he procrastinates when it comes to tidying up./ Lucas, Arlo, and Findley have a day of make-believe with the clouds./ Arlo can't resist the temptation to look into next door's garden through a knothole.

added.title: Run, Mushpie, Run
added.description: Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit notice that Mushpie seems in great shape lately. They want to feel as great as she does and try to discover her secret. When they realise that she works out every morning, our friends decide to join her. And soon, all the Mushables do too. Now Lilit notices that Mushpie doesn't seem in such great shape anymore.

added.title: Watch the Storm
added.description: When Chep asks Mush-Mush and Lilit to go storm-watching and they refuse, Lilit feels bad and convinces Mush-Mush to join their friend. But there are no storms on the horizon. When they notice Chanterelle going through the forest mysteriously, our Mushlers decide to find out what she's up to instead. That's when a big storm starts brewing on the horizon.

added.title: Say What?
added.description: When Share magically has her voice stolen from her in a field of flowers, she and the other Bears must learn to listen so they can find her voice and solve the problem between the flowers and their Whiffle gardeners.

added.title: The Big Freeze
added.description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself.

removed.title: Toy Party
removed.description: Bing and Hoppity, Pando and Bullabaloo are all having a tea party at Sula and Hippoty's today! But what will happen when Sula gives Bullabaloo more cake than Hoppity, and Bing thinks that's not fair?

removed.title: Hide and Surprise!
removed.description: While playing hide and seek with Percy, Diesel accidentally gets stranded on a barge that floats out to sea, where it becomes a group effort to rescue him.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Good Vibrations
removed.description: Lilit is under pressure. Truff, the most talented musician in Mushton, has invited her, Mush-Mush and Chep to form a band with him. Only problem is they can hardly play music! Truff insists: they just need to relax and feel the groove. But when Truff tells his new band they will perform at the Food Snail, Lilit isn't relaxed at all!

removed.title: Flying/Dr. Lucas is in the House/Arlo's Portrait
removed.description: After watching Findley in flight, Lucas wonders what it would be like to fly./ Dr. Lucas tries to make all his friends feel better but ends up under the weather himself./ Lucas decides to paint a portrait of Arlo. But Arlo can't sit still.

removed.title: Fruit & Vegetables
removed.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

removed.title: Get Lost Loula
removed.description: Let's play Hide and Seek! Pocoyo is the seeker and is brilliant at it - but only thanks to Loula. When Loula gets all the praise for being a super-seeker, Pocoyo is jealous. He throws a ball very far away to make Loula run off and chase it. His friends think it was a nasty thing to do and so Pocoyo feels bad and decides he must now find Loula. They follow her footprints but she's gone really far and they just can't find her anywhere. Finally at an island in the sea they despair: they think she's gone forever. But we can already see that Loula is safe and sound. Everyone is reunited and Pocoyo can celebrate being a super-seeker too, after all.

removed.title: Pato's Egg
removed.description: Pato finds an egg and immediately falls in love with it: he wants to take care of the little baby inside the egg. When the egg hatches he gets the shock of his life: it's not a cute little duckling at all, but a very odd looking spider. His friends are terrified of the little creature and won't play with Pato if he brings it along. Pato rather craftily and meanly makes the little spider go away and do things on its own, so Pato can play with Pocoyo and Elly. Finally the little spider makes their hearts melt when he shows them that there's nothing to be scared of and he just wants to be their friend.

removed.title: Cell Phone
removed.description: Bing and Hoppity want to play with Talking Lettuce on Flops cell phone. Bing remembers to put the cell phone down when he wants to voosh with Hoppity. But what happens when Bing vooshes a little too close to Flop's cell phone?

removed.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
removed.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

removed.title: Planets
removed.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

removed.title: The Last Laugh
removed.description: Disappointed when his friends don't laugh at his jokes, Funshine encounters the Laffinpuff, a magical comedian who grants Funshine's wish to make everyone think he's funny. But Funshine realizes it's no fun being funny when people laugh at everything he says, whether he means it to be funny or not. To get the wish rescinded, he must face the Laffinpuff in a grueling ordeal of slapstick humor.

removed.title: Bye Bye
removed.description: Bing loves playing with his new orange balloon, but what will happen when he bounces on it too much?

removed.title: Fireworks
removed.description: Bing is excited to watch the Fireworks outside, but will they be too noisy loud?

removed.title: Dance Off!
removed.description: Pocoyo and Pato stumble upon a disco and Elly is the DJ. Pato gets grooving to a track and Elly thinks he's fantastic. But Pocoyo's not impressed. He has a go and shows his dance. It's wonderful, but then Pato thinks he can do even better. And so it goes on - an impromptu, ever-so-funky dance off! Things get out of hand when Pocoyo is raving and Pato is body-popping so Elly changes the record. She takes to the dance floor and shows the rivals - in an uncannily Britney-esque way - that instead of competing, they can all have fun dancing together! It's much more fun.

removed.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
removed.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

removed.title: An Alien Christmas Carol
removed.description: The angry Martian hates Christmas since his father disappeared one Christmas Eve and he's decided to use his cannon to ruin Christmas for Pocoyo and his friends. But you never know what life has in store. After all, everyone has a heart.

removed.title: Special Delivery
removed.description: Chep knows so many things about nature that Mush-Mush and Lilit are confident he's not far from being an expert like Mushpot. So, when Travel Snail seems unwell, Mush-Mush and Lilit encourage their friend to take care of her in Mushpot's absence. Chep's diagnosis takes everyone by surprise: Travel Snail is expecting baby snails! At least that's what Chep is convinced about.

removed.title: Out of the Cheer Zone
removed.description: Two mischievous Whiffle kids come to play with Dibble, forcing Cheer to put her important work on hold to manage them. When she finds her "managing kids" skills lacking and her important work in jeopardy, she uses her skills as a leader to get the kids working as a team to help her complete her work while having fun at the same time.

removed.title: A Rusty Rescue
removed.description: When Thomas throws away Diesel's favorite oil can thinking it's trash, he makes a promise to get it back and learns it's better not to touch things that aren't yours.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Old Macdonald
removed.description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

removed.title: Christmas Tree
removed.description: It's Christmas time and Pato wants to decorate a Christmas tree. He can't bring himself to fell an innocent fern, but with a bit of ingenuity and a lot of team work the gang manages to find the perfect tree. Merry Christmas!

removed.title: Show
removed.description: Bing and his friends are at the bandstand in the park when they all decide to put on a show! And Bing's singing the Rainybow song for the finale! But what will happen when Bing doesn't like everybody looking at him?

removed.title: Shake the Apple Tree
removed.description: It's the end of the summer and the trees are full of delicious apples ready to be picked!

removed.title: Boot Castle/Avocado's Long Time Out/Tanks Giving
removed.description: Findley discovers a boot that him and Lucas use as a castle./ When they hear Avocado has been put in her naughty crate, Lucas and Findley entertain her./ Lucas brings Dimples things from around the house so she doesn't feel left out.
